Class Context

  • java.lang.Object
    • oracle.iam.identity.icf.foundation.logging.AbstractLoggable<T>
      • oracle.iam.identity.icf.dbms.DatabaseContext
        • oracle.iam.identity.icf.connector.openfire.Context
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    oracle.iam.identity.icf.foundation.logging.Loggable

    public class Context
extends oracle.iam.identity.icf.dbms.DatabaseContext
    The Context wraps the JDBC connection.

    Define the test method meaning the wrapped connection is still valid.
    Defines come useful method to work with prepared statements.

    Since:
    1.0.0.0
    Version:

      • searchTime

        public final oracle.iam.identity.icf.dbms.DatabaseFilter searchTime(java.lang.Long timestamp)
        Returns the filter that has to be applied on an incremental search.

        Note:
        The value passed in is usually define in the operational options of a search operation of the connector. Due to the limits of ICF there isn't any capability to transfer Date values. Only Long values can pass the serialization interfaces.
        For that reason this method accepts a Long value.

        Parameters:
        timestamp - the time after that an account in the target system should be created or modified to be included in the returning collection.
        Allowed object is Long.
        Returns:
        a DatabaseFilter to be applied on a search for user accounts.
        Possible object is DatabaseFilter.
